original: Kinman, Eva Ingrid Margareta, läroverksadjunkt, Strömsnäsbruk, f. 19/ 2/06 i Eksjö av överjägmäst. J. E. Kinman o. h. h. f. Bergenström. — Stud :-ex. i Linköp. 26, fil. kand. i Upps. 31, fil. mag.- 32, provår i Sthlm 40. Resor t. Schweiz 26, Tyskl. 30 o. 34, Engl. 35, Frankr. 37. Timlär. i Boden 33-34, i Borås 35-36, vik. adj. i Arvika 36-37, vik. ämneslär. i Vadstena 37, e. adj. där 38, i Sala 38-39, Ange 39, Växjö 41, Piteå 41, Gudmundrå 42, adj. i moders,m., tyska o. franska v. Strömis-näsbruks samrealsk. sed. 47.
translated: Kinman, Eva Ingrid Margareta, high school teacher, Strömsnäsbruk, b. 19/2/06 in Eksjö to Chief Inspector J. E. Kinman and H. H. F. Bergenström. — Studied: high school examination in Linköping in 1926, Bachelor of Arts in Uppsala in 1931, Master's degree in 1932, probationary year in Stockholm in 1940. Traveled to Switzerland in 1926, Germany in 1930 and 1934, England in 1935, and France in 1937. Hourly teacher in Boden from 1933-1934, in Borås from 1935-1936, substitute teacher in Arvika from 1936-1937, substitute subject teacher in Vadstena in 1937, permanent teacher there in 1938, in Sala from 1938-1939, Ange in 1939, Växjö in 1941, Piteå in 1941, Gudmundrå in 1942. Teacher of mother tongue, German, and French at Strömsnäsbruk's secondary school since 1947.

occupation.name: Teacher of mother tongue, German, and French
